      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=18821#M18821</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Rogue flat out blows away mages when it comes to raids on DPS at the endgame.&amp;nbsp; During the original era mage is better due to the lack of gear, but thats only going to last a couple months.&amp;nbsp; Once rogues get the ragebringer, which is about 1/10 the difficulty of the mage epic, they become king dps.&amp;nbsp; With further expansions and better weapons, the gap between mage and rogue dps widens even further.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Also you have to add in the fact that most end game guilds wont allow the mage to use a pet on certain raids when there are AEs and what not.&amp;nbsp; A ninja afk or a few seconds of not paying attention can mean the raid wiping.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think when you decide what class you want to play (in your case between mage and rogue) you need to look at whats funnest for you, not whats going to be most useful to other people.&amp;nbsp; Think of yourself: do you enjoy playing a caster or a melee?&amp;nbsp; Do you really want a pet?&amp;nbsp; Do you want to be able to see the most increases from getting that new weapon?&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
