&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I'm not trying to dis mages or any other caster class as i love them all, but rogues and other melees have a great deal more to do in a raid or grp than : Attkon, bs/bs/evade/bs.&amp;nbsp; There are a ton of discs and weapon types that require a lot of timing, thought and knowledge of when and how to use.&amp;nbsp; Playing a melee has as much going on as any caster class with the possible exception of bards, mh and ccers.&amp;nbsp; With rogues this is especially true as the goal is to balance the maximum dps while at the same time avoiding agro.&amp;nbsp; It is a lot more involved than just hitting evade each time you see the mobs face and new mobs in new zones require constant repositioning in order to maintain good dps.&amp;nbsp; A rogue at the high end is actually a great deal of work to play properly.</description>
