      <description>I didn't mean to say rogues are easy to play on raids, just that they&#xD;
only have one role on raids until Luclin.&amp;nbsp; You can break it into a&#xD;
hundred steps, covering every minute detail, or you can generalize it&#xD;
in a few words.&amp;nbsp; EQ is a very repetitive game.&amp;nbsp; By the time you've&#xD;
leveled a class to 60 and raided a bit all the small things become&#xD;
second nature.&amp;nbsp; You know where you need to be and if you are out of&#xD;
position, you know when its safe to go all out, you know when you need&#xD;
to hold back, you know when to use duelist,&amp;nbsp; and you know when to use&#xD;
counterattack or nimble (etc..).&amp;nbsp; There is still a lot of moving and&#xD;
buttons that need pushing, but there's no longer any critical thinking&#xD;
tied to it.&amp;nbsp; It was a challenge initially, but you've learned how to&#xD;
DPS efficiently, and now its just repetition.&amp;nbsp; You know how to react to&#xD;
any changes, and if a new situation comes up you have the tools to&#xD;
adapt to it.&amp;nbsp; It's the same with mages, it's the same with every&#xD;
class.&amp;nbsp; If asked, you can explain exactly why you took every action,&#xD;
but all that went through your head before you took the action was&#xD;
"____ happened, I need to ____."&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
