      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Rogue all the way, IMO.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Like everything there are tradeoffs......Really depends on waht you want to do.&amp;nbsp; If you want to be pure DPS go rogue.&amp;nbsp; If you want to be able to solo, go mage.&amp;nbsp; If you don't want your dps to be situational, go rogue.&amp;nbsp; If you want to have really nice utility go mage.&amp;nbsp; If you don't want a lot of limitations in certain raid situations, a mage is going to have problems, where a rogue is going to have very very few problems raiding if ever.&amp;nbsp; BTW, I don't know what this guy is talking about with rogues havign problems with AoEs in PoP.....There's AA for that too.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mages are excellent DPS and have a lot of utility but it's mana based, pet based, and nukes can be resisted.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Until you can get pet AAs you will likely be asked not to summon your pet on a lot of raids.&amp;nbsp; Your ability to do DPS will be based on available mana.&amp;nbsp; You will also need separate buffs for your pet until you get AA for group buffs too.&amp;nbsp; But, your pet is a monster and they get really good later on, so if you like to be able to solo, a Mage might be for you.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Whereas a rogue properly played is total raw dps power that is basicly unlimited.&amp;nbsp; A rogue in crappy gear and minimal AA just slides down the dps scale a bit.....A rogue in great gear with a lot of AA is a total DPS machine.&amp;nbsp; But both are still unlimited raw dps to a group or raid.&amp;nbsp; But you wont be soloing much if at all.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It's all about tradeoffs and you have to decide what it is you really want to do.&amp;nbsp; Personally, I prefer melees to robed casters, and I particularly don't like playing pet classes myself, so it would be a no brainer for me.&amp;nbsp; Go rogue.&amp;nbsp; You ever meet a rogue who didn't just LOVE it? :)&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
