      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Nimbledy wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Massimo_Bertoxx wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If you don't want your dps to be situational, go rogue.&amp;nbsp; ...&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;Rogue is a fabulously fun class.&amp;nbsp; But do recall that rogue dps is cut &lt;EM&gt;substantially&lt;/EM&gt; if you don't have the mob's back and can't backstab, so it is rather situational in that respect.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Technically, yes, but this doesn't really happen that much.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Because of ripostes and the like, ALL melee dps should&amp;nbsp;be given the back of&amp;nbsp;a mob and that is where they really need to be.&amp;nbsp; If you are consistently not getting the backs of mobs then your tanks aren't doing their jobs very well and this should be addressed by whoever in your guild is leading raids/tanks.&amp;nbsp; Not that there aren't exceptions but for the most part, tanks need to be firmly positioning mobs so that the back is accessable for reasons beyond just giving rogues a target.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Also, there are AAs that overcome this as well for rogues....Chaotic stab and its upgrades lessen the directional loss in DPS for rogues a great deal.&amp;nbsp; With the right AAs a rogue can even assassinate from the front.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In addition, even without backstabbing, rogues are on the highest melee damage tables available for normal melee hits, so even without access to a mobs back, they will still be doing as much dps as any other melee class minus special attacks.&amp;nbsp; Again this is even less of a factor when a rogue has the chaotic stab AAs.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;For sustained unconditional DPS, Rogues really do rule.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Massimo_Bertoxx on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;06-12-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;11:22 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
